HEADWORD: Peucil
<hw>Peu"cil</hw> <pr>(p⟦umac⟧"s⟦icr⟧l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>pey`kh</grk> pine tree.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A liquid
resembling camphene, obtained by treating turpentine hydrochloride with
lime.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>peucyl</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

